      "site_admin": true
    },
    "created_at": "2017-02-14T00:55:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-14T00:55:32Z",
    "body": "> So to clarify, the only way to display remote content through <webview> is to go against the security checklist which recommends that we disable nodeIntegration in all renderers through webPreferences?\r\n\r\nNo, the `<webview>` and `BrowserWindow` run in separate renderers so node integration should be disabled in whatever one(s) are loading remote content.\r\n\r\nA `BrowerWindow` loading a `file://` URL is not considered remote content, but if that file contains a `<webview>` tag that loads a `http://` URL then node integration should be disabled on that `<webview>` tag directly."
  },
